dct_title_s: The anchoring places at Old Harbour, Long's Wharf, Salt River, Peake Bay and Walker's Bay [map]
dct_description_sm: Shows Portland Bight, formerly Old Harbour Bay. Relief shown by hachures; depths shown by soundings. Includes 3 views of landscape features, lettered for reference. "457." In upper left-hand corner: Hydrographical Office. Historic Maps copy has label on verso: West Indies. Old Harbor, Long's Wharf, Salt River, Peake Bay, and Walker Bay Anchorages. 457.
dct_publisher_sm: [London] : Published according to Act of Parliament by Capt. Hurd RN, Hydrographer to the Admiralty, 7th. Novr. 1815.
